Dockerizing Mongodb Database:

1. Create a container named mongodb-container and the database is locally running on port 27017 and built by using the official image mongo.
docker run --name mongodb-container -p 27017:27017  --rm -d mongo

2. To clear all the containers not in use
docker container prune 

3.Check the logs to see whether mongo container is communicating locally to mongodb database.
docker ps mongdb-container
